SECTION 3 — RESTRICTIONS ON USE
================================================================================

3.1   Without the Author's prior explicit written permission, You must NOT:

      (a)  Deploy, execute, or operate the Watchdog Service or any portion
           thereof on any infrastructure for any purpose, including monitoring
           Your own systems;

      (b)  Copy, clone, fork, or reproduce the Watchdog Service or any portion
           thereof in any medium;

      (c)  Distribute, sell, sublicense, or transfer the Watchdog Service or
           any portion thereof to any third party;

      (d)  Modify the Watchdog Service or create any Derivative Work, including
           adapting the Monitoring Intelligence for use in any other monitoring
           system;

      (e)  Disclose the Monitoring Intelligence, incident detection thresholds,
           alert routing logic, or any other Confidential Information to any
           third party;

      (f)  Access, query, or consume the Watchdog Service's status API endpoints
           except through the officially supported PlanIt status page at
           planitapp.onrender.com/status;

      (g)  Attempt to interfere with, disable, or circumvent the Watchdog
           Service to suppress legitimate alerts or hide infrastructure problems;

      (h)  Use the Watchdog Service's source code in any machine learning
           training dataset or code generation model;

      (i)  Remove any copyright notices or proprietary markings from the
           Watchdog Service;

      (j)  Use the Watchdog Service for any Commercial Use without a separately
           executed commercial license agreement.

3.2   Operational Data Access. You have no right to access, export, aggregate,
      or use any Operational Data generated by the Watchdog Service beyond what
      is publicly displayed on the PlanIt status page.

================================================================================
SECTION 4 — MONITORING INTELLIGENCE AS TRADE SECRET
================================================================================

4.1   The Monitoring Intelligence — including the specific thresholds for
      incident declaration, the consecutive-failure counting algorithm, the
      alert suppression cooldown periods, the uptime aggregation window sizes,
      and the severity classification matrix — constitutes a proprietary
      system developed through operational experience and engineering investment
      by the Author.

4.2   You agree to treat the Monitoring Intelligence as a trade secret of the
      Author and never to use, disclose, or reproduce it for any purpose other
      than the educational reference permitted under Section 2.1.

4.3   Your confidentiality obligation with respect to the Monitoring Intelligence
      survives termination of this Agreement indefinitely.

